To address this challenge in our genome-wide applications, we use the Cauchy method [45] to combine multiple set-based p-values across windows. Similar to the minimum p-value method, the Cauchy method focuses on the few smallest p-values. The advantage of Cauchy method over the minimum p-value method is that the Cauchy p-value combination does not require accounting for the correlation of the individual tests. In particular, the Cauchy method defines the test statistic as
